data.title: FINNISHED 1 - quirky covers from Finland edited & reworked
data.meta_description:
FINNISHED 1 - quirky covers from Finland edited & reworked by Darthfunkel, released 26 March 2024

1. Taas Nousen Junaan (Darthfunkel Edit) - I Shot The Sheriff by Kirka & The Islanders)
2. Tahdon Miehen (Darthfunkel Edit) - I Need A Man by Marja Koski)
3. Salapoliisin Tytär (Darthfunkel Edit) - Son of a Preacher Man by Jouko & Kosti)
4. Miltä Meno Maistuu (Darthfunkel Edit) - Walk on the Wild Side by Lasse Mårtenson)
5. Rokkibaby (Darthfunkel Edit) - Rock Your Baby - Rolf Bergström & Pyhimykset)

"Finnished 1" includes five DJ edits of Finnish cover versions of globally known hits. Get yourself some unexpected tracks for the eccentric dancefloor!

Track 1 : Special DJ edit of a Finnish cover of Bob Marley's I Shot The Sheriff by Kirka and the Islanders from 1975.
"Taas nousen junaan" is Finnish for "I board the train again"

Track 2 :Special DJ edit of a Finnish cover of Eartha Kitt's I need a Man by Marja Koski from 1984.
"Tahdon Miehen" is Finnish for "I Want a Man"

Track 3 : Special DJ edit of a Finnish cover of Dusty Springfield's Son of a Preacher Man by Jouko & Kosti from 1969.
"Salapoliisin tytär" is Finnish for "Daughter of a Private Detective"

Track 4 : Special DJ edit of a Finnish cover of Lou Reed's Walk on the Wild Side by Lasse Mårtenson from 1973.
"Miltä Meno Maistuu" is Finnish for "How Does the Going Taste"

Track 5 : Special DJ edit of a Finnish cover of George McCrae's Rock Your Baby by Rolf Bergström & Pyhimykset from 1975.
"Rokkibaby" is Finnish for "Rock Baby"

This is the first installment of FINNISHED.
